Description: Egypt, crowd of European male and female adults "at the races", Heliopolis. Small group of Egyptian adult males standing in foreground. Large building with semi-circular annex and arches at rear. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
